24 July 2017 Government Communication and Information System will on Wednesday, 26 July 2017 hold a Memorial Service in honour of the veteran government communicator, Mr Ronnie Mamoepa who passed away on Saturday, 22 July 2017. The memorial service will be attended by the Minister of Communications, Ayanda Dlodlo, the GCIS management and government communicators from three spheres of government. Members of the media and government communicators are cordially invited to attend the event and share memories and celebrate Ronnie Mamoepa’s life. Date:  Wednesday, 26 July 2017 Time: 09:00Venue: 1035 Tshedimosetso House, Corner Francis Baard & Festival Street, GCIS, Hatfield in Pretoria RSVPs should be forwarded to Ms Ireen Magwai on email: ireen@gcis.gov.za by Tuesday, 25 July 2017 at 12h00. Share your tribute messages and memories using the hashtag #RIPRonnie Enquiries: Phumla Williams Cell: 083 501 0139 Issued by Government Communication and Information System